<br>
If you play a wizard,<br>
and you play all the way up to level 60,<br>
and you manage to cast a spell for 8 seconds,<br>
without getting interrupted<br>
or killed<br>
and without your target walking out of range<br>
You deserve to do a shitload of damage.<br>
<br>
Period.<br>
<br>
And the other guy, if he has not invested in the many items that will deflect or absorb your nuke, deserves to DIE on impact.<br>
<br>
Anyway Garrison's is not the ultimate PvP nuke; that's Manaburn. Manaburn casts faster, and unlike Garrison's it really -does- kill on contact.<br>
<br>
The existance of manaburn confirms that VI (finally) thinks that we should be able to kill in one shot, provided we can survive long enough to make that shot. I agree. It is a weapon we -deserve- as wizards, it doesn't sound one bit overpowered to me. At least 3 classes have an invulnerability spell to try and negate our burn. Enchanters have unresistable mesmerize &amp; manadrain. Necros can try to beat us to the draw with Lifeburn. Most others have a fighting chance to interrupt us. -Everybody- can run beyond casting range in 6 seconds, if they invest in a horse.<br>
<br>
But at least wizards are no longer simply -incapable- of inflicting fatal damage. Finally we have access to deadly force, and it becomes the job of the enemy to try and prevent us from using it. That's how it should be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 426<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/4/02 7:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shadows of Luclin: Spell Discussion.</span><hr size=1> For PvP, a 7.5 or 8 second casting time would make the level 60 DD spells  useless unless you surprise the target.<br>
<br>
In PvE, since many mobs break fetter after one DD spell is cast, being able to do a LOT in one spell makes the new spells a lot more useful.  Especially with mobs that have a high movement speed, being able to do LOTS in one shot also saves you mana by not forcing you to re-root.  Also, in groups where mobs drop very quickly, and you can't get more than one shot in anyway, what's better, one big nuke that you start to cast early, or TRYING to cast two faster casting spells?  It's obvious that the one big nuke is better for us in most situations.  Remember also that once you are level 60(which you need), many will have their epics, which will help with any agro generated.<br>
<br>
I would have liked to see another 1800+ damage spell that was cold based to round out the line of these big blast type spells as well.<br>
<br>
For those who are looking for more damage at lower levels, spellcasting fury probably should have been made available as a skill starting at level 34 and wizard only, with a 252 cap being 100 percent of the time.  Damage upgrade would max at around 10 to 15 percent and would &quot;stack&quot; with the alternate advancement boost we get which has the 33,66,and 100 percent damage &quot;bonus&quot;.  <br>
<br>
In this way, it gives a nice boost in the level range that wizards have a problem in, would let people see our damage when we crit, but would also improve things even in the pre-60 range where most feel some improvements to damage output are needed.<br>
